Displayes this string over his head until selected

Character name is Maegel.
Character is a skeleton.
This character is summoned by the player clicking on the hanging chain in the last room of the bear caves.
This character appears in front of the sarcophagus in the middle of the shaft of light. 
The character displays a single string over his head until he is spoken to.
The character presents a riddle to the player. Failure to answer the riddle correctly, or canceling the dialogue before attempting to answer results in damage and this character disappearing. He reappears when summoned again by clicking on the chain. Quitting the dialogue anywhere but the correct answer causes damage, and the character disappears until summoned again..
If this character is attacked, a blast of fire is fired out and he disappears until summoned again. This character cannot be fought, and the only way to unlock the sarcophagus is to answer his riddle.
Correctly answering the riddle causes the character to leave, and allows the player to access the sarcophagus. 
If the player clicks on the chain while the sarcophagus is open, and ALL the items are still inside it, this character appears again with a single string over it's hed, and then disappears.

The item in the sarcophagus should be one with an old description, one that is at least a several hundred years old.

Character should have the following description:
A skeleton stands before you, devoid of flesh and discolored with age. Tattered rags hang from its shoulders, obviously not designed with the intent of spending centuries in a damp tomb. If the creature had eyes, you would swear it looked hopeful... almost desperate.
Player has clicked on the hanging chain with the sarcophagus unlocked, and everything is still inside it. Does not happen if the player pretended to be on the big quest.
